ZCZC GE27
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 052300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A BROAD AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL DOMINATE ACROSS CULLERCOATS
CENTRED 1025 IN THE BALTIC SEA. AT THE SAME TIME AN ATLANTIC LOW PRESSURE
SYSTEM WILL ALSO BE CENTRED 987 TO THE S OF ICELAND MOV NE WITH HIGH PRESSURE
NEAR THE AZORES. ON TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY THE BALTIC HIGH WILL GRADUALLY
RECEDE NEWARDS WITH THE LOW CLEARING NE AS A FURTHER DPN LOW MOVS E IN
THE ATLANTIC OCEAN. THIS WILL BE CENTRED 968 TO THE W OF THE BRITISH ISLES
BY EARLY WEDNESDAY THEN DRIFTING N TO BE CENTRED TO THE SW OF ICELAND BY
THURSDAY EVENING. A RIDGE WILL ALSO EXTEND NE FM THE AZORES ACROSS THE S
OF THE UK AND TOWARDS SCANDINAVIA. NO GALES ARE CURRENTLY EXP ACROSS CULLERCOATS
DURING THE PERIOD ALTHOUGH SPELLS OF STRG WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS VIKING AND
N UTSIRE ON WEDNESDAY AND FAIR ISLE ON THURSDAY
